name: FUNERALOPOLIS
description:
This painting represents how a person with 
mental disorder (in some cases) may internalize
mental illness stigma and experience diminished
self-esteem and self-efficacy. They see themselves
as a failure, unworthy, horrible, ugly, etc.

Oil, acrylic, gouache on paper + digital. 



*Funeralopolis is a song from one of my
favorite bands, Electric Wizard.
The name stands for the meaning of 
‘lifeless, sickness, death, and decay.’
